    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>No one ever in India or Bangladesh said that, but some guy in England thought I was the Mother Teresa of economics. My God, that absolutely raises my temperature to the boiling point because I think economists didn&rsquo;t lack a heart&mdash;I don&rsquo;t think that&rsquo;s quite the case&mdash;and secondly, Mother Teresa didn&rsquo;t do technical work at all and I don&rsquo;t deny the importance of technical work, and thirdly, she sacrificed her life all the time, which I have not done. I&rsquo;ve always lived in comfortable quarters with a reasonable salary... without feeling guilty. I&rsquo;m no schizophrenic. It&rsquo;s not the motivation thing. We&rsquo;re talking about whether the market fundamentalists were right or wrong in their theory, that&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;re talking about and you cannot solve it by referring the matter to the heart, you have to refer the matter to your head.</p>
<p>Watch the interview online at www.dukechronicle.com.</p>

